      <div class="bio-content">
        <h1>Indochinese Tiger</h1>
        <p class="status endangered big">Endangered</p>
        <p><strong>Estimated remaining:</strong> ~350</p>

        <h3>Habitat</h3>
        <p>Forests of Thailand, Myanmar, Laos, Vietnam, and Cambodia, preferring remote, hilly or mountainous forests with good cover and water sources.</p>

        <h3>Threats</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Intensive poaching for illegal trade</li>
          <li>Habitat loss from agriculture and development</li>
          <li>Snaring crisis across Southeast Asia</li>
          <li>Prey depletion from hunting</li>
          <li>Weak law enforcement in some range countries</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Conservation efforts</h3>
        <p>Thailand's Western Forest Complex provides one of the last strongholds. Increased anti-snaring patrols. Camera trap monitoring to track populations. Regional cooperation through ASEAN Wildlife Enforcement Network. Community engagement to reduce human-tiger conflict.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
